ID: for records in the BDRC database, indicate it here (ex: P123), for duplicates, indicate all IDs, for records not in the BDRC database, create an ID starting with P1TMP (ex: P1TMP123)
names_tib: coma separated list of names in Tibetan, prefilled witht the primary name in the BDRC database
names_skt: coma-separated list of Sanskrit names, in IAST. BDRC has very sparse data of this kind and this has been prefilled with some strings from Otani and Tibskrit
ambiguity: add X here if the person is ambiguous and if the data is uncertain
roles: ma = main author, pa = pandita, tr = translator
